    "Continue"
    # [Scene: Saltwood Cliffs | Two Weeks Later — Dusk]
    hide nyla_torres
    hide maya_serrin
    hide dr_elena_park

    scene bg ch4_453e40_5 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The small rustle of settling sand, the distant murmur of the village, Old Man Cala's voice carrying]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Rising strings — restrained, hopeful, urgent]
    "The weeks fold into a blistering rhythm. Funding arrives in slow drip — community-led grants matched with town labor. There are nights when the lab cot is a thin claim to rest; there are mornings when"
    "your knees complain and your hands remember every pull of the shovel. The work is raw and exacting: burlap-wrapped brush cores, reed gates lashed at prescribed intervals, a hundred small adjustments to keep tides from turning"
    "weapons into disasters."
    "Little things begin to happen in ways that feel enormous. A gull makes a tentative scrape in the reformed reeds and tucks its wing around an egg. Teenagers who once took shifts complaining now trade stories"
    "with Old Man Cala about the dune of his childhood; his voice turns their scoffs into fascination. An elderly ferry operator brings hot bread to the nursery as thanks — small human economies of care assembling"
    "around the work."
    "You taste hope, and the taste is briny and stubborn. It is not celebratory; it is a steady, inward warmth that does not pretend the risk is gone. A storm season still looms. The work is"
    "not finished. But the dune has a spine beginning to form; the boardwalk folds its new channels like careful breathing; the marsh's reeds hold a whisper of more water than before without panicking."
    "Aiden Koa finds you at dusk, hands still smelling of tar, and for a long moment neither of you speaks. He watches the gull, watches the teens clustered around Old Man Cala, watches you watching —"
    "and somewhere in the patience he carries, a decision seems to settle rather than wrestle."
    show aiden_koa at left:
        zoom 0.7

    aiden_koa "You were right to start it. It's...it's something."
    show maya_serrin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrin "It's the only thing I could start with the people here."
    "He takes your hand briefly — a contact that is neither a promise nor a contract, simply a shore-to-shore touch. It steadies. It does not resolve every fear, but it is enough in the small ledge of a day that has not swallowed everything."
    "You pin the tide-watch back into your pocket. You map tomorrow's tidelines on the station glass, the chalk tracking forward like a pulse. Your body protests. Your heart hums with tiredness and something like cautious satisfaction."
    "You close your eyes for a breath and taste that stubborn hope again — briny, finite, real."
    hide aiden_koa
    hide maya_serrin

    scene bg ch4_453e40_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single held note, bright but not untroubled]
    "You breathe in and let the small, living things of the town fill the room: gulls, teenagers, Old Man Cala's stories, Nyla's laugh, Aiden's steady weight. The dunes are commitments, not guarantees. You fit your shoulder to them because someone has to."

    scene bg ch4_453e40_7 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fade Out]

    jump chapter5
